The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) for distributed storage systems (DSSs), which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of non-MDS linear codes in DSSs is a topic in distributed storage (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses PIR protocols, which can fall under security and privacy (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SI).
